**1. Stock Blender lets you attach arbitrary custom properties to objects:**

![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/94753/137398792-671a4f86-61dd-4805-841a-0a70ce9fcae0.png)
![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/94753/137398858-e8ab1228-2135-4d7f-bbce-984b755839d0.png)

**2. Once defined, those properties show up (and can be adjusted) right within information panel:**

![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/94753/137399272-dceea4eb-a6f9-4038-a86d-4c3ebe1c3c90.png)

**3. During glTF export there is an "Include Custom Properties" option:**

![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/94753/137399362-c799798f-f329-41ff-9c77-0205436635b5.png)

**4. Custom properties are reflected as `extras` on the glTF node:**

```diff
{
    "asset" : {
        "generator" : "Khronos glTF Blender I/O v1.5.17",
        "version" : "2.0"
    },
    "scene" : 0,
    "scenes" : [ {
            "name" : "Scene",
            "nodes" : [ 0, 1, 2 ]
        } ],
    "nodes" : [
        {
+            "extras" : {
+                "prop" : 1
+            }, 
            "mesh" : 0,
            "name" : "Cube"
        },
        {
            "name" : "Light", 
            "...": "..."
        }
  ]
}
```
